<br>
Quillimane's cloak is indeed very rare.  I'm proud to say that our guild necro just happened to be running by SK and saw him up, took him down and looted this fine item.  You never realize how much you need levitate until your party that is dungeon crawling doesn't have a levitation class (ie., Tower of Frozen Shadow)! <p>Trinnity X'Vex <BR>
Shadowknight <BR>
Indigo Void <BR>
Firiona Vie <BR><BR>
"For Hate's sake, I spit at thee..."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uevangelinanife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Evangelina Nife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I'm the princess, okay?</span><br>  Posts: 510<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 7:47:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=843.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB - Boots or EQ with a Levitation Proc</span><hr size=1>    Singing steel boots (Bard only) have a right click effect that will cast levitate on the whole party that lasts for 5 minutes.  It's unlimited use, so it's great for fighting in tower of Frozen shadows n such.<br>
<br>
   As far as your wizard goes, your best bet is either buying levitation potions, or finding a magician friend to summon you some rings (not many magicians on FV though).  <br>
<br>
   Quillmane's cloak is really rare, and as it's used in the magician epic, also quite expensive to purchase.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uartillis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artillis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 8:03:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=843.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB - Boots or EQ with a Levitation Proc</span><hr size=1> Quilmane is your best bet for a item that casts levitate, I'm also a proud owner of a peguses feather cloak.  Funny thing is quillmane spawned like 3 times in a row.  First time someone else got it, second time I got it, Third time it flew by me while I was still OOM from the previous killing of it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
Now becase the peguses feather cloak is part of the mage eppic I personaly don't think it's fair to camp and take quilmane if a mage is already in the zone hunting the beast and you know it.  The thing is a level 30 mob so that means that this part of the mage eppic goes trivial once the mage hits level 41-43 and its a rare.<br>
<br>
My other thing to point out is your a wizard as am I, you can cast the spell levitate and don't need a item.  If you don't like collecting bat wings you can purchase them from the caster guild in freeport for about 2gp a stack.<br>
<br>
The peguses feather cloak is a nice little item but it's kind of like a horse, not a big deal to have but nice all the same.  <br>
<br>
